It all began at a military munitions storage facility, where the teenagers frequently went to as their local 'lovers lane'. One night, several tenagers were chased from the area by what the described as a seven foot humanoid creature with wings and glowing red eyes. The creature was able to keep up with them even as they drove away in their cars at high speeds; and the legend of the Mothman was born. As the weeks and months wore on, dozens and dozens of paranormal sightings and happenings were observed and reorted by almost the entire town. Even the drivers of a Red Cross Blodmobile truck reported being chased one night! <br>
<br>
One particularly interesting Mothman sighting was forwarded by a elderly woman who reported a daylight encounter. She said she was watching tv when there seemed to be some interference with the picture. She went to the door of her house, and an object hovering over the ground. She described it much like a large robot with two red sensors and some sort of hovering device that emmited a high pitched droning sound. She says she never felt like she was in any danger, and there was no attempt at communication. She recalled turning back into the house and the tv was working again, but another program was almost over, indicating almost 40 minutes had passed, despite her view that the whole encounter only took two minutes at the most.<br>
<br>
UFO reports, animal mutilations, disappearing pets, flying Mothmen and other mechanical robot-looking devices; the whole town was abuzz with unusual sightings. <br>
<br>
Then the Men In Black sightings began. One MIB witness noted that their ears were oddly shaped, not human-like at all. Another noted that they seemed highly inquisitive aout perfectly normal everyday objects and things. For instance, one MIB, seen in a local diner, was fascinated with Jell-O. Another MIB witness noted when interviewed about the events 20 years later, that their actions reminded him of the Coneheads on Saturday Night Live.   <br>
<br>
The paranormal events stopped as suddenly as they started on the night of December 15, 1967. The Silver Bridge spanning the Ohio River in the center of town, collapsed during the evening rush hour, claiming 46 lives. It was as if the jolt of real horror from the bridge collapse had awakened the town from a surreal nightmare filled with gargoyles and monsters.<br>
<br>
The events surrounding the Mothman legacy were thoroughly investigated 20 years later by John Keel and turned into his book <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>  'The Mothman Prophecies'</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  and now it's been turned into a movie of the same name. One of the things that struck Keel and his team of investigators was how little wavering there was in the re-telling of the encounters by the witnesses 20 years later. Over time, one would think any hoaxers would fess up to their deeds, as it really wouldn't matter anymore. However, virtually everyone that was interviewed stuck by their original sighting.<br>
<br>
So what really happened here? Some speculate that the entire town was somehow unknowingly involved in a top secret government experiment using LSD and various mind control techniques. Such experiments were certainly happening at the time, usualy in University settings in controlled experiments with student volunteers. But what if the government wanted a larger test audience? Far fetched? Maybe, but how else could one account for an entire town's involvement and deep rooted belief in the reality of the events so long after they happened. Or maybe the event's really did happen as described. Giant flying Mothmen,UFOs, MIBs, robots, all of it really did happen.  <br>
<br>
The events of Point Pleasant were and still are a benchmark for every serious paranormal investigator to ponder, and the one prominent case that has defied reational explanaton to date.    <p><center><img src=http://jawjrfotofile.homestead.com/files/Psybanner.jpg></center><br><br><img src=http://jawjrfotofile.homestead.com/files/rainbow_laser.gif><br></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesfrm32.showPrevMessage?topicID=100.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesfrm32.showNextMessage?topicID=100.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=100.topic&index=7><img src=http://web.ukonline.co.uk/unexplained.m/images/addreply.jpeg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesfrm32.emailToFriend?topicID=100.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesfrm32.threadControl?topicID=100.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesfrm32.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=100.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesfrm32.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=100.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub16.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellsp